The paper deals with information inequalities, which are typically studied in the field of information theory (cs.IT). It also involves cryptography (cs.CR) as the authors mention the use of inequalities in cryptography. The method proposed in the paper involves linear programming and optimization, which are commonly used in the fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI) as the authors mention the potential applications of their method in analyzing network data.
